《'''人事'''》（[[英語|英語]]：Human Events<ref name="张小娟内幕出版社2015">{{cite book|author1=张小娟|author2=内幕出版社|title=《中共治国术》|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LMvvCAAAQBAJ&pg=PT154|date=2015年5月29日|publisher=[[内幕出版社|内幕出版社]]|isbn=978-1-63032-838-2|pages=154–|access-date=2020年7月8日|archive-date=2020年7月17日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200717064824/https://books.google.com/books?id=LMvvCAAAQBAJ&pg=PT154|dead-url=no}}</ref>），又译作《'''人类事件'''》<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.epochtimes.com/gb/20/2/24/n11892806.htm|title=【思想领袖】美政府应在大学保障言论自由|date=2020-04-06|publisher=[[大纪元时报|大纪元时报]]|accessdate=2020-07-09|archive-date=2020-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200916210121/https://www.epochtimes.com/gb/20/2/24/n11892806.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，是[[美国|美国]]持[[保守主义|保守主义]]立场的聚焦[[政治|政治]][[新闻|新闻]]与[[分析|分析]]的[[报纸|报纸]]及[[网站|网站]]，印刷版报纸创刊于1944年2月2日<ref>{{cite web|url=https://reason.com/1978/02/01/the-course-of-human-events/|title=In the Course of "Human Events"|date=Feb 1, 1978|publisher=[[Reason_Magazine|Reason Magazine]]|accessdate=2020-07-09|archive-date=2020-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820055759/https://reason.com/1978/02/01/the-course-of-human-events/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，2013年成为一份纯数字出版物。该杂志的名称来源于美国《[[独立宣言|独立宣言]]》的第一句话：“在'''人'''类历史'''事'''件的进程中……<ref name="刘复之1993">{{cite book|author=刘复之|title=人权大辞典|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YPp3AAAAIAAJ|year=1993|publisher=[[武汉大学出版社|武汉大学出版社]]|pages=846–|access-date=2020-07-09|archive-date=2020-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200717151623/https://books.google.com/books?id=YPp3AAAAIAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>”（When in the course of '''human events'''...）<ref name=washtimes>{{cite web|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2013/feb/27/human-events-shutter-newspaper-after-70-years/|title=Valerie Richardson, "Stop the Presses! Human Events to shutter newspaper after 70 years," February 27, 2013|work=[[Washington_Times|Washington Times]]|4=|accessdate=2020-07-09|archive-date=2020-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200808022153/https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2013/feb/27/human-events-shutter-newspaper-after-70-years/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。该杂志在[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]]出版，由[[菲利普斯出版公司|菲利普斯出版公司]]的[[子公司|子公司]][[雷格纳里出版公司|雷格纳里出版公司]]的所有者[[伊戈出版公司|伊戈出版公司]]（Eagle Publishing, Inc.）出版。

==发展历史==
《人事》由1933年至1940年担任《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》编辑的[[菲利克斯·莫利|菲利克斯·莫利]]、[[弗兰克·哈尼根|弗兰克·哈尼根]]、资深记者[[詹姆斯·威克|詹姆斯·威克]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1964/11/08/archives/james-wick-dies-publisher-was-67-editor-of-human-events-a.html|title=JAMES WICK DIES; PUBLISHER WAS 67; Editor of Human Events, a Conservative Newsletter|date=1964-11-08|publisher=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2020-07-09|archive-date=2020-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107035234/https://www.nytimes.com/1964/11/08/archives/james-wick-dies-publisher-was-67-editor-of-human-events-a.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>和[[前新政主义者|前新政主义者]]（New Dealer）<ref>{{cite news |title=Henry Regnery, 84, Ground-Breaking Conservative Publisher |author=Robert McC. Thomas Jr. |newspaper=The New York Times |date=June 23, 1996 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/06/23/us/henry-regnery-84-ground-breaking-conservative-publisher.html |accessdate=2020-07-09 |archive-date=2020-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123194419/https://www.nytimes.com/1996/06/23/us/henry-regnery-84-ground-breaking-conservative-publisher.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[亨利·雷格纳里|亨利·雷格纳里]]于1944年创立<ref>Gillian Peele, American Conservatism in Historical Perspective, in Crisis of Conservatism? The Republican Party, the Conservative Movement, & American Politics After Bush, Gillian Peele, Joel D. Aberbach (eds.), Oxford: [[Oxford_University_Press|Oxford University Press]], 2011, p. 21</ref>。

==对罗纳德·里根的影响==
《里根总统：想象的胜利》（President Reagan: The Triumph of Imagination）作者[[理查德·里夫斯|理查德·里夫斯]]（Richard Reeves）在书中写道，《人事》周刊是美国前总统[[罗纳德·里根|罗纳德·里根]]“多年来最喜欢的读物”<ref name="Reeves2005">{{cite book|author=Richard Reeves|title=President Reagan: The Triumph of Imagination|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C1kvsToagGEC&pg=PA24|date=23 December 2005|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=978-0-7432-8230-7|pages=24–|access-date=2020-07-09|archive-date=2020-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929235720/https://books.google.com/books?id=C1kvsToagGEC&pg=PA24|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在1986年的[[雷克雅未克峰会|雷克雅未克峰会]]上，里根总统对时任[[苏联共产党总书记|苏联共产党总书记]][[米哈伊尔·戈尔巴乔夫|戈尔巴乔夫]]说，他不能放弃[[星球大战计划|星球大战计划]]，因为“这些年来最直言不讳地批评苏联的人”<ref>{{cite book|author=Richard Reeves|title=President Reagan: The Triumph of Imagination|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C1kvsToagGEC&pg=PA351|date=23 December 2005|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=978-0-7432-8230-7|pages=351–|access-date=2020-07-09|archive-date=2020-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929235722/https://books.google.com/books?id=C1kvsToagGEC&pg=PA351|dead-url=no}}</ref>——他提到了他最喜欢的报纸《人事》——“会踢爆我的脑袋”<ref name="Ratnesar2009">{{cite book|author=Romesh Ratnesar|title=Tear Down This Wall: A City, a President, and the Speech that Ended the|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tVy_vABsrisC&pg=PA83|date=3 November 2009|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=978-1-4391-7005-2|pages=83–|access-date=2020-07-09|archive-date=2020-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718195713/https://books.google.com/books?id=tVy_vABsrisC&pg=PA83|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

